{"title": "Hold the Unsolicited Ingredient", "content": "A gag in which a character orders food, then specifically asks that a certain ingredient be excluded, even though that ingredient is either not commonly found or ordered in that food to begin with, or is typically only added on request.\n\nA common use of this joke is with pizza and anchovies: Characters will specifically ask for \"no anchovies\" as if failing to do so would inevitably cause them to appear on the pizza \u0097 highly unlikely. Onions are another (un)popular choice for use in this trope, especially when ordering sandwiches (though they do tend to be a default ingredient of many sandwiches - it depends on the restaurant, of course).\n\nStarting in The New '10s, pineapple is getting more attention regarding pizza toppings.\n\nHatred for certain pizza toppings (or food additions) in general probably falls under Stock \"Yuck!\" or Does Not Like Spam.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HoldTheUnsolicitedIngredient", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TwentyOneJumpStreet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TheFiresignTheatre", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/InsideOut", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TeenageMutantNinjaTurtles1990", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SuperMarioBros", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GoodBurger", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/AmberBrown", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheClueFinders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TwentyOneJumpStreet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheElectricCompany1971", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Supernatural", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ALF", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MorecambeAndWise", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheSuperMarioBrosSuperShow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/TomSmith", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Splatoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Splatoon2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/IrregularWebcomic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/PennyArcade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/HouseOfMouse", "/pmwiki/pmwik